description: Lie on your back and grab the line behind your head with both hands. Hook one foot under the line and roll around the line landing again in Backbounce.
Two Hammock Rolls in one bounce.
Three Hammock Rolls in one bounce.
Do a Hammock Roll and finish with a Back Roll in the same bounce.
Roll down to Backbounce.
Hammock Roll going directly to Feet.

technicalName: Hammock Roll from Feet to Feet
description: Hammock Roll starting from Feet and going directly back to Feet.
Double Roll down to Backbounce.
From Backbounce pull yourself to the back over your shoulder and land in Korean.
tips: Have the leash on the same side as the shoulder you roll over.

description: From Backbounce do a Back Roll but stop in Shoulderstand.

technicalName: Half Back Roll to Shoulder Roll
description: Do a Half Back Roll but add a Shoulder Roll to finish the trick.
Back Roll directly into Backbounce.
From standing you jump back and roll over your shoulder to land in Korean.
tips: Have the leash on the same side as the shoulder you roll over.

description: Do a Back Roll and go directly to Feet.
Do a 180 and then go into a Back Roll from Feet.
This often happens when you try a normal Back Roll with bad timing.
Do a Back Roll from Feet but with a roll around the line as well.
From Backbounce move forward like you are going to Chest but add a Chest Roll.

technicalName: Back Roll from Feet to Feet
description: The highline freestyle Backflip! As the name implies it is a Back Roll from Feet to Feet.
From Backbounce get back up into Korean and in one fluid motion kick one leg over the line to go into a Sofa Roll.
From Backbounce perform a Richy Roll but land directly to Feet.
From Backbounce swing one leg to one side and roll around the line on the other side to perform a Panic Roll.
From Backbounce do a Panic Roll to Feet.
With both hands on the line supporting your weight you lie on your belly and roll forward around the line.
With both hands on the line supporting your weight you lie on your belly and roll backward around the line.
From Belly turn one time around the line and land in Exposure in one bounce.
Do a Belly Roll to Feet but rolling backwards.

technicalName: Korean 270 Spin to Back Belly Roll
description: Spin like you would do a flowflip (without the rotation) but then finish with a back belly roll.
Hang in Nevermind but with the hands opposing each other. Thread the leg that is free through your leg and the closer arm and kick through to go to Back Belly Roll.
Makako landing in Exposure.
From lying on your chest get some momentum with your free arm and then roll around the line grabbing it with both hands. Land back in chest.
tips: You can wrap the foot around the line to avoid falling away from the line.

description: From lying on your chest get some momentum with your free arm and then roll around the line grabbing it with both hands. Land back in chest.
tips: You can wrap the foot around the line to avoid falling away from the line.

description: Do a Chest Roll and in the end of the roll push yourself away from the line to put your feet on.
Do a Back Chest Roll and in the end of the roll push yourself away from the line to put your feet on.
Do a Chest Roll and in the same bounce a 180 Chest Flatspin to Feet.
Do a Chest Roll and in the same bounce a 360 Chest Flatspin.
Wrap your foot around the line to get a good hook and then do a Chest Roll without your hands.
tips: Try to not use your shoulder or arm to keep the line near your body.

description: From standing you turn 360 and land in Chest.
From standing you turn 360 while doing a roll around the line and land in Chest.
Almighty Flip but instead of hooking the line with your foot you grab and pull on the leash.
From Exposure grab the line with both hands and roll around the line landing back in Exposure.
tips: Try to wait a bit after hitting the bottom of the bounce before you start with the trick. If you start too early you will kill the bounce.

description: From Exposure grab the line with both hands and roll around the line backwards landing back in Exposure.
tips: Try to wait a bit after hitting the bottom of the bounce before you start with the trick. If you start too early you will kill the bounce.

description: From your normal stance grab the line with both hands and roll around the line landing back in the starting position.
From your normal stance grab the line with both hands and roll around the line backwards landing back in the starting position.
Double Barrel Roll.
From standing in switch you spin 180 by just turning your feet (no stepping). Then do an Adrenaline Roll but when you are landing, turn your feet again to not land in Exposure but in normal stance.
tips: Either start or land in switch.

description: From your regular stance do a frontside 270 and roll around the line like you would for a Flowflip. Try to land back in your normal stance and not in Exposure.
Two Yoda Rolls in one bounce.
Two Back Yoda Rolls in one bounce.
Three Back Yoda Rolls in one bounce.
From Exposure do a front flip while hooking one foot under the line and putting it back on the line for the landing.
tips: After 270 deg of rotation try to pull the line under yourself with your feet.

description: This one is for heros only!
Double Front Almighty Flip.
tips: Stay open for the first one and tuck for the second one to get good momentum.

description: Do a 180 and then go into a Front Almighty Flip.
Starting in switch stance you do a 270 spin and go into a Front Almighty Flip in the end turn 90 to look back at the same anchor where you started.
From Exposure do a back flip while hooking one foot under the line and putting it back on the line for the landing.
tips: First lean back and then kick/hook the line.

description: Double Back Almighty Flip
tips: Do the first one laid out and tuck for the second one to get good momentum.; Try to get the hook at your ankle. If the line is near your toes it's hard to pull it around for the second roll.

technicalName: Panic Roll from Feet to Feet
description: Do a 90 with restepping and go into a Yoda Roll.
Do a Yoda Roll but during the roll fully pop your feet off and then go back on the line
Almighty flip but from normal stance.
Like the barrel almighty flip but flipping the other direction.
From Exposure do a 180 and during the spin go into the Yoda Roll.
Sit in Korean, grab the line in front of you with both hands and let yourself fall to the side.
tips: Keep your legs straight and push them together.

description: Do a Back Korean Roll but the legs go away from the line so you can go to Sofa when landing.
Do a Back Korean Roll but the legs go away from the line in order to turn 180 and land back in Korean looking at the other anchor.
It's a Back Korean Roll and a 360 at the same time.

technicalName: One Leg Sit Roll to Feet
description: From One Leg Sit you roll to the side in the direction of your leg that is on the line and land to Feet in normal stance.
From One Leg Sit you roll to the side in the direction of your leg that is hanging down and land to Feet in normal stance.
From sitting position (one legged) you do two rolls to the side and land on your feet in normal stance.
Do a Can of Soup and a 270 at the same time.
From standing let the line come to your kneepit and roll to the side landing in korean.

technicalName: Korean Roll from Feet to Feet
description: Do a Korean Roll but starting from Feet and landing to Feet.
From the catch position (Nevermind) stand back up.
Do a Nevermind with a Chest Roll and then swing your leg over to end in Sofa.
Do a Nevermind up but instead of going to Feet you turn 360 and land in Chest.
Grab the line with one hand, bring it around your body by passing it to your other hand and land in Korean.
Do a 180 and then an Orbital.
Grab the line with one hand, bring it around your body by passing it to your other hand and then land in Exposure.
Orbital to Feet but with a 360 spin.
Orbital to Sofa but starting in Exposure.
From Sofa you spin 270 to land in Korean (or Chest) and combine it with a roll around the line.
tips: Sit in Sofa position grab the line to the side of you with hands facing behind you. On the way up dive down where your hands are and roll around the line. Land in Korean or Chest.

description: Panic Roll but landing to Feet.
tips: During the roll get your far foot on the line. At the end of the roll get your second foot up on the line.

description: Panic Roll with an additional Chest Roll landing to Feet.
You do a Panic Roll to Feet but don't use your hands to hold the line. Instead use your foot to hook the line and go to Feet.
Do a Panic Roll but before you land throw your second leg on the other side of the line as well to land back in Sofa.
From Backbounce go into the Panic Roll to Feet.
Do the Panic Roll but instead of landing in Chest you go into Shoulderstand.
tips: Regrab with one hand to land comfortably in Shoulderstand.

description: Similar to a Panic Roll but you start from Korean turned 90 further away to where you want to go.
tips: Grab the line behind your back and let yourself fall backwards. The rest happens by magic!

description: Flowflip but landing to Feet in Exposure.
tips: During the flip get your far foot on the line. At the end of the flip get your second foot up on the line.

description: From Hanging fly up to exposure.
tips: Get some momentum with your legs in the bottom part of the bounce. As soon as you are weightless pull the line below your feet.; This trick doesn't require as much strength as you would think! It's all about getting enough momentum with your legs.; If you can't hold the bounce in the hanging position try again with less bounce.

description: From Hanging fly up to Sofa.
From Hanging go up to shoulder stand.
tips: When dropping down to Rocket already grab with the hands as you would for the Shoulderstand then you don't have to regrab.

description: Rocket Mount with a 180.
tips: The movement in the end is comparable to the Sofa 360 to Feet.

technicalName: Rocket Mount to Back Sofa Roll
description: From Hanging swing your legs beside your hands (similar to a Sick Nasty movement) and go into a Back Sofa Roll.
Rocket Mount with a 360.
tips: First spin a little bit into the opposite direction to then explode out the way you really want to spin.; Try to avoid doing a Rocket Mount 180 and then restep with your feet but go for the 360 right away.

technicalName: Rocket Mount Side Roll to Sofa
description: From Rocket Mount do a Side Roll with the axis of rotation perpendicular to the line and land in Sofa.
tips: Flip one of your hands to allow for a better initiation of the momentum.

description: Start by doing a Rocket Mount but then go into a Belly Roll finishing with a 180 to Sofa.
tips: Get a lot of momentum for the Rocket Roll and in the end do a 180 and stick your butt out as in the Sofa Roll 360.

description: Rocket Rewind with an additional Back Sofa Roll in the end.
From Hanging get a lot of momentum with your feet and do one front roll around the line and land in Exposure.
From hanging get a lot of momentum with your feet and do one back roll around the line and land in exposure.
From Rocket do a 360 around an axis perpendicular to the line and land again in Rocket.
From the Rocket you kick your feet trough your arms between the line and your body, regrab the line and land back in Rocket.
Do a Shrimpflip 180 but then go to Feet.
In Rocket do a backflip, completely letting go of the line and landing back in Rocket.
It's a mix between Rocket Mount and Nevermind.
tips: From Hanging use the bounce to get your feet up to the line and mantle in the same bounce.

description: Obi Wan but you go up behind the line.
tips: Bring the foot that does not go to the line straight away far over the line to get your center of gravity right over the line and then put it on the line in the end of the trick.

description: Do a 360 while hanging under the line.

Go up behind the line in a Double Drop Knee position but then fully extend your upper body and upper legs while keeping the line at your ankles behind your back. Roll around the line and end up back in Hanging.
Like a Rocket Mount but go up behind the line.
tips: Sam and Ian have quite different techniques for this trick. Try both and see which one suits you (or do your own variation of course).

description: From Rocket do a Reverse Rocket Mount but instead of going to Feet you land in Sofa.

technicalName: Reverse Rocket Mount to Double Drop Knee
description: From Hanging do a Reverse Rocket Mount but land in Double Drop Knee.
From Rocket you do a front flip motion releasing one hand and land with your kneepits hanging on the line.
Antihero but landing in Sofa.
From Exposure you grab the line with one hand and roll forward. As soon as you are under the line you perform a regular Antihero.
From Exposure you grab the line with one hand and roll forward. As soon as you are under the line you perform an Antihero to Sofa.
Like an Antihero to Sofa but landing in Exposure.
From Exposure do a front flip off the line and catch the line to land in Rocket.
From Shoulderstand roll to one side and land back in Shoulderstand.
From Shoulderstand roll to one side and get your feet on the line. Land in Exposure.
From Standing drop to Shoulderstand.
From Shoulderstand roll over your back to land in Korean.
tips: If you are on the right shoulder try to thread your right arm through the leash so you don't end up with the leash stuck on your shoulder.

description: From Standing do a frontflip across the line and land in Korean.
tips: Thread your arm through the leash so it is not wrapped around your shoulder.

description: From Standing you turn 180 and do a Frontroll from Feet.
Start by doing a Chest Roll and then do a Front Roll by pushing with one foot off the line.
From Sofa you grab the line next to you with both hands and swing the legs over the line and around behind you and again over the line on the other side of your hands back to Sofa.
From Sofa you grab the line next to you with both hands and swing the legs over the line and around behind you and then you land in Exposure on the other side of your hands.
Do a Sick Nasty but with a 180.
Do a Sick Nasty 180 with an additional Front Sofa Roll. The motions happen at the same time rather than one after each other.
Do a Sick Nasty but with a 180 landing in Exposure.
Start with the motion of a Sick Nasty 180 but keep spinning and do a full 360 landing back in the starting position.
Tre Nasty landing in Chest.
Sick Nasty Roll but starting from Korean.
Sick Nasty with an additional Back Sofa Roll in the same bounce.
tips: Regrab with the far hand to get into the Back Sofa Roll.

description: Start with a Sick Nasty Roll but instead of swinging both your legs over the line again put one foot on the line and keep the other one behind the line. Then put the second foot on and stick the trick.
Sick Nasty Roll with an additional Back Sofa Roll in the same bounce.
Sit in Sofa, grab the line with both hands and press the line against your body. Then let yourself fall to the front.
Sit in Sofa, grab the line with both hands and press the line against your body. Then let yourself fall backward.
tips: Leash to the side can help prevent bad falls.; If you fall into a backlever position try to not hold on to the line in order to save your shoulders.

description: From Korean let yourself fall to the side and immediately after you start the roll swing one leg over the line to finish the roll as a Sofa Roll.
Same as Richy Roll but going into a Back Sofa Roll.
From standing in Exposure go down to Sofa.
tips: Let your feet come towards your body, grab the line and then let your feet go.; As a pre-exercise try to just touch the line while bouncing in Exposure. This will help you control the line a lot better.; Don't just drop down to the line with your legs straight, bring the line towards your body in a controlled way.

description: From Sofa stand up to Exposure.
tips: Get one foot on the line and let go with the arm on the same side. Then press yourself up with this foot and the other hand and get your second foot on the line.

description: Start like you would do a Panic Roll but in the end stick your butt out and land in Sofa.
Do a Sofa Roll 360 but go to Feet and land in Exposure.
From Sofa you do a 360 and then land in Exposure
From Sofa you do a Sofa 360 to Feet but add a 180 in the end.
tips: Try to not do the 360 and then restep to get the 540 but instead go for the 540 directly.

description: Do a Sofa Roll 360 with an additional Back Sofa Roll in the end.
tips: You have to be fast with the regrab.

description: Sit in Sofa and roll to the side over your neck back to Sofa.
tips: There are more comfortable tricks to try.

description: Start in Sofa. Both hands next to you (right or left) holding on to the line. Then do a Sofa Roll with your body leaning towards the line where your hands are.
tips: Stay small and compact during the roll.

description: Double Sofa Roll landing in Exposure.
Spin 540 on the line in a standing position.

technicalName: Double Drop Knee Roll to Feet
description: From Double Drop Knee do a roll and stand up to land in Exposure.

technicalName: Inward Drop Knee Spin to Front Sofa Roll
description: Start from Inward Drop Knee and spin 270 to go into a Front Sofa Roll.
Double Roll in Double Drop Knee.
Start in Sofa facing the anchor, spin 360 behind you down to Chest.
Freefall with a Roll. Similar to Panic Roll but starting in Sofa facing the other anchor.
Frodo Roll to Feet.
Roll down to Frodo.
Buddha Roll.
Starting in Frodo do a roll and land in Buddha.
Sick Nasty landing in Chest.
Sick Nasty to Chest Roll.
In one bounce do a Frontroll starting from Feet and landing back to Feet.
tips: Longer lines allow for more time to execute the trick.
